# Design System Rules

## Color Usage
CRITICAL: Always use CSS custom properties (var()) for colors. Never use hardcoded hex values.

### Semantic Color Tokens
Use theme tokens (--text, --surface, --border, etc.) instead of primitive colors:
- Text: var(--text), var(--text-subtle), var(--text-active), var(--text-placeholder), var(--text-disabled)
- Surfaces: var(--surface), var(--surface-hover), var(--surface-active), var(--surface-raised), var(--surface-low)
- Borders: var(--border), var(--border-active), var(--border-transparent)
- Interactive: var(--link), var(--link-hover), var(--focus)

### Status Colors
- Success: var(--success-text), var(--success-surface), var(--success-border)
- Info: var(--info-text), var(--info-surface), var(--info-border)
- Danger: var(--danger-text), var(--danger-surface), var(--danger-border)
- Warning: var(--warning-text), var(--warning-surface), var(--warning-border)

### Brand Colors
- Primary: var(--brand-primary), var(--brand-primary-hover), var(--brand-primary-text)
- Secondary: var(--brand-secondary), var(--brand-secondary-hover), var(--brand-secondary-text)

## Border Radius
- Default: 4px
- Large elements (dialogs, modals): 8px
- Use border-radius property directly with px values

## Best Practices
- Never use hardcoded color values - always use CSS custom properties
- Theme tokens automatically handle light/dark mode switching
- Use semantic tokens (--text, --surface) over primitives (--grey-grey-900)
- Hover states should use corresponding -hover tokens
- Active/selected states should use -active tokens
- Disabled states should use -disabled tokens

## Component Patterns
- Buttons: Use var(--brand-primary) background with var(--brand-primary-text) for primary actions
- Cards: Use var(--surface-raised) with var(--border) and border-radius: 4px
- Forms: Use var(--field) for input backgrounds, var(--text-placeholder) for placeholders
- Alerts: Match background/text/border using corresponding status tokens (success, info, danger, warning)